<br>
The reason for me posting this is to show why things are done a certain way. A way that Peritus apparently does not understand and I hope that one day they do understand. An early lesson I learned in EQ is that 2 raids in 1 zone can often lead to problems no matter how good the intentions are at the beginning. This is usually why only one guild is found raiding in each zone unless the spawns they are after are far apart and guilds entry into the zone is planned to avoid confusion. Apply some common sense and I believe most would agree with me. As an example, Azure Legion's last Chardok raid was delayed for several hours because Dominion was either headed to the royals or were already there. Azure Legion dispursed to do other things while I kept in touch with their raid leader. As it neared time for them to leave Azure Legion assembled in Chardok and got CoHed down to the king room by a Dominion mage.<br>
<br>
As an added note on August 29th Azure Legion entered Fear to obtain the Shissir for an enchanter epic. It was nearly a full hour before Pertius showed up, moved past us, then pulled and killed the Shissir. All the while ignoring any attempts to communicate with them. This matter still remains unresolved with Verant and may never see any action taken.<br>
<br>
And now we have this past Saturday...<br>
<br>
